00:30:11.078 --> 00:30:13.515
- Closet. Dad's apartment.

753
00:30:13.548 --> 00:30:14.582
They're beating him up.

754
00:30:14.616 --> 00:30:15.883
- I can get your money.

755
00:30:15.916 --> 00:30:18.152
Just one more day.
like two tops.

756
00:30:18.185 --> 00:30:20.321
Wait. wait. wait. wait. no.

757
00:30:20.354 --> 00:30:22.022
- All right. stay hidden
until we get there.

758
00:30:22.056 --> 00:30:23.991
- I can't.

759
00:30:24.024 --> 00:30:26.293
They'll kill him.
I have to do something.

760
00:30:26.327 --> 00:30:27.394
- No. Dash.

761
00:30:27.428 --> 00:30:29.531
<i>Dash. no.</i>

762
00:30:32.366 --> 00:30:34.068
- I know how you
can get your money.

763
00:30:34.101 --> 00:30:35.336
- Who the hell is this?

764
00:30:35.369 --> 00:30:37.237
- It's my neighbor.
He waters my plants.

765
00:30:41.342 --> 00:30:42.610
- You are such a liar.

766
00:30:42.644 --> 00:30:46.046
Although lying to protect
your kid is almost noble.

767
00:30:46.080 --> 00:30:48.215
Be ashamed if I had to
break all his teeth.

768
00:30:48.248 --> 00:30:49.617
stomp both his hands into soup.

769
00:30:49.651 --> 00:30:52.486
- Pass and pass.

770
00:30:52.520 --> 00:30:55.055
How about we go
with my plan instead--

771
00:30:55.089 --> 00:30:57.358
rob a bunch of rich kids
that go to my school?

772
00:30:57.391 --> 00:30:59.326
<i>Who wants a Rolex?</i>

773
00:31:01.328 --> 00:31:03.497
- You better not be lying. kid.

774
00:31:03.531 --> 00:31:05.199
Your dad is out of free passes.

775
00:31:07.535 --> 00:31:09.504
Let's go.

776
00:31:13.407 --> 00:31:15.510
- Dash would never knowingly
put someone in danger.

777
00:31:15.543 --> 00:31:16.944
- So we track down whether

778
00:31:16.977 --> 00:31:18.646
any school families
are out of town.

779
00:31:18.680 --> 00:31:20.214
- The Laporte premiere.

780
00:31:20.247 --> 00:31:22.383
He's a pretentious
auteur filmmaker.

781
00:31:22.416 --> 00:31:23.618
His new movie launches tonight.

782
00:31:23.651 --> 00:31:25.252
Autumn Harrington is in it.

783
00:31:25.285 --> 00:31:26.920
That's the girl that
Dash has a crush on.

784
00:31:26.954 --> 00:31:28.155
Her address is in the system.

785
00:31:32.560 --> 00:31:34.928
- Damn. who is this chick?
- Autumn?

786
00:31:34.962 --> 00:31:36.964
She's an up-and-coming it girl.

787
00:31:36.997 --> 00:31:38.533
Her new project's
getting Oscar buzz.

788
00:31:38.566 --> 00:31:42.670
- Yeah. well. let's hope she
get paid in diamond bracelets.

789
00:31:42.704 --> 00:31:44.371
you know.
stuff that's easy to pawn.

790
00:31:44.405 --> 00:31:47.274
Otherwise.
you and dad gonna find out

791
00:31:47.307 --> 00:31:50.010
what a landfill tastes like.

792
00:31:50.043 --> 00:31:51.111
Out.

793
00:31:55.182 --> 00:31:57.017
Stay with Gus
until I give you the signal.

794
00:31:57.050 --> 00:31:58.452
- All right.

795
00:32:00.187 --> 00:32:02.557
- Man. for what it's worth.
your dad is the biggest

796
00:32:02.590 --> 00:32:04.391
train wreck I ever met.

797
00:32:04.425 --> 00:32:06.561
My old man. he in prison--

798
00:32:06.594 --> 00:32:08.663
trying to steal a FedEx plane
with a tow truck.

799
00:32:08.696 --> 00:32:10.364
- Well. if you're the
ghost of my future self.

800
00:32:10.397 --> 00:32:12.199
I might just have to
Virginia Woolf it.

801
00:32:13.601 --> 00:32:15.035
- I don't know what that means.

802
00:32:15.068 --> 00:32:16.270
- She was arguably
the most influential

803
00:32:16.303 --> 00:32:18.439
writer of the 20th century?

804
00:32:18.472 --> 00:32:19.707
Ended it all by
walking into a river

805
00:32:19.741 --> 00:32:21.308
with rocks in her pockets.

806
00:32:24.178 --> 00:32:26.313
- Nobody likes a comedian. kid.

807
00:32:26.346 --> 00:32:28.949
- I'd argue. but the gun
gives you the last word.

808
00:32:32.019 --> 00:32:35.189
- Hey. if this is a set-up.
I'm killing everybody. got it?

809
00:32:35.222 --> 00:32:36.591
- Yes. sir.

810
00:32:40.728 --> 00:32:43.330
- You're not my Agedashi tofu.

811
00:32:43.363 --> 00:32:45.165
- You're not
supposed to be here.

812
00:32:45.199 --> 00:32:46.133
- Well. he cut me
out of the movie.

813
00:32:46.166 --> 00:32:47.401
so I wasn't on the list.

814
00:32:47.434 --> 00:32:50.270
Do you know how
mortifying that--

815
00:32:50.304 --> 00:32:52.339
who the hell are you?
- Hey. who else in the house?

816
00:32:52.372 --> 00:32:55.209
- Nobody.
My parents are in Monaco.

817
00:32:55.242 --> 00:32:56.611
- All right. get over here.

818
00:32:56.644 --> 00:32:58.345
- I don't want to.

819
00:32:58.378 --> 00:33:00.214
- No problem.
I'll just shoot you.

820
00:33:06.487 --> 00:33:08.590
Hold hands.
- Why?

821
00:33:08.623 --> 00:33:11.091
- Whoa. it's even
bigger on the inside.

822
00:33:11.124 --> 00:33:14.061
See. this is the kind of place
I'm gonna get when I get paid.

823
00:33:14.094 --> 00:33:15.462
- Hey. man. shut up.

824
00:33:15.496 --> 00:33:17.097
Stay down here
with the idiot. all right?

825
00:33:17.130 --> 00:33:18.131
Steal anything that's shiny.

826
00:33:22.135 --> 00:33:23.638
Now take me to
your parents' room.

827
00:33:23.671 --> 00:33:25.105
And they better have a boatload
of watches and jewelry.

828
00:33:25.138 --> 00:33:26.608
- Hey. hey!
- Let's go.

829
00:33:26.641 --> 00:33:28.208
- Whoa. those whiskey bottles
worth. like. 500 each.

830
00:33:28.242 --> 00:33:29.109
I'm just gonna grab a couple.

831
00:33:29.142 --> 00:33:30.645
- Show me.

832
00:33:35.783 --> 00:33:37.084
- What about this?

833
00:33:37.117 --> 00:33:38.018
- The Merlot? Really?

834
00:33:38.051 --> 00:33:38.786
No. dude. those two
are worth way more.

835
00:33:49.697 --> 00:33:52.032
All right. all right.

836
00:34:24.832 --> 00:34:25.700
- Hey. where's the jewelry?

837
00:34:25.733 --> 00:34:27.301
- Closet.

838
00:34:27.334 --> 00:34:29.303
- All right. all right.
Come here.

839
00:34:29.336 --> 00:34:31.171
Hey. hey. stay here.

840
00:34:41.481 --> 00:34:43.585
- I cannot believe you
brought them to my house.

841
00:34:43.618 --> 00:34:44.686
- I panicked. okay?

842
00:34:44.719 --> 00:34:46.320
They were gonna kill my dad.

843
00:34:46.353 --> 00:34:48.255
And besides. you weren't
supposed to be here.

844
00:34:48.288 --> 00:34:50.190
I would never knowingly
put you in danger.

845
00:34:50.223 --> 00:34:52.159
- Because you have
the hots for me.

846
00:34:52.192 --> 00:34:54.662
- I have romantic
intentions. yeah.

847
00:34:54.696 --> 00:34:56.463
But clearly.
you don't share them. so--

848
00:34:56.496 --> 00:34:59.333
It's not like you're not cute.

849
00:34:59.366 --> 00:35:01.168
You're just--
- Poor?

850
00:35:01.201 --> 00:35:02.202
- Exactly.

851
00:35:07.742 --> 00:35:08.710
What are you doing?

852
00:35:08.743 --> 00:35:10.344
- Looking for a gun.

853
00:35:10.377 --> 00:35:11.579
Oh. that's not a gun.

854
00:35:11.613 --> 00:35:12.880
- Oh.
- Oh.

855
00:35:12.914 --> 00:35:14.281
Oh. your parents are freaky.

856
00:35:14.314 --> 00:35:15.617
- Hey. what the hell you doing?

857
00:35:15.650 --> 00:35:17.417
Get away from there.
- Oh. sorry.

858
00:35:17.451 --> 00:35:20.220
Sorry.

859
00:35:20.253 --> 00:35:22.189
- I'm never gonna be able
to look at my parents

860
00:35:22.222 --> 00:35:23.490
in the eye again.

861
00:35:23.524 --> 00:35:25.459
- Me neither.

862
00:35:25.492 --> 00:35:27.461
- Hey. Andre wouldn't
really hurt my kid. right?

863
00:35:27.494 --> 00:35:29.363
This is a scare tactic?

864
00:35:29.396 --> 00:35:32.867
I mean. I know I'm not a great
dad. but I try. you know?

865
00:35:32.900 --> 00:35:35.369
When it's convenient for me.

866
00:35:35.402 --> 00:35:36.638
Like. I wanna be better.

867
00:35:36.671 --> 00:35:37.772
Like. I really do.

868
00:35:37.805 --> 00:35:39.473
I think about it all the time.

869
00:35:39.507 --> 00:35:42.342
Well. not all the time.

870
00:35:42.376 --> 00:35:44.646
which is the heart
of the problem. really.

871
00:35:44.679 --> 00:35:45.780
I just gotta be better.

872
00:35:45.813 --> 00:35:49.617
The kid deserves a role model.
not the flaming hot mess

873
00:35:49.651 --> 00:35:51.919
I am on a daily basis.

874
00:35:51.953 --> 00:35:53.621
It feels really good
to come clean about this.

875
00:35:53.655 --> 00:35:55.623
you know.
it's kind of cathartic--augh!

876
00:35:55.657 --> 00:35:56.724
When the hell did you get here?

877
00:35:56.758 --> 00:35:57.792
- Where's Dash?

878
00:35:57.825 --> 00:35:59.226
- Let's go.

879
00:35:59.259 --> 00:36:00.795
- No. she's staying here.

880
00:36:00.828 --> 00:36:02.496
She hasn't seen your face.
so you're in the clear.

881
00:36:02.530 --> 00:36:03.798
Just. you can do
whatever you wanna me.

882
00:36:03.831 --> 00:36:04.866
Just let her go.

883
00:36:04.899 --> 00:36:06.668
- Hey. man. you got balls.
kid. unlike your father.

884
00:36:06.701 --> 00:36:07.669
But she cannot stay
here. all right?

885
00:36:07.702 --> 00:36:09.369
Let's go.

886
00:36:09.403 --> 00:36:10.270
- There's a gold bar
in that bedside table.

887
00:36:10.303 --> 00:36:11.405
- Yeah. right.

888
00:36:11.438 --> 00:36:12.507
- I'm serious.

889
00:36:12.540 --> 00:36:14.809
But if you wanna leave it.
like...

890
00:36:14.842 --> 00:36:16.410
- Stay right here.

891
00:36:16.443 --> 00:36:17.578
Don't move.

892
00:36:20.715 --> 00:36:22.817
Oh!

893
00:36:22.850 --> 00:36:24.552
- Get back.

894
00:36:24.585 --> 00:36:27.387
Drop it.

895
00:36:27.421 --> 00:36:28.956
Come on. get up.

896
00:36:30.323 --> 00:36:31.826
Hey. you two okay?

897
00:36:31.859 --> 00:36:33.895
- Physically.

898
00:36:33.928 --> 00:36:36.296
- Here. Give me these.

899
00:36:36.329 --> 00:36:37.765
Come here.

900
00:36:37.799 --> 00:36:38.833
- Ow.

901
00:36:38.866 --> 00:36:40.568
Thanks.

902
00:36:40.601 --> 00:36:42.637
And thanks for
trying to save me.

903
00:36:42.670 --> 00:36:43.905
- Yeah. anytime.

904
00:36:43.938 --> 00:36:46.641
- Oh. thank God.

905
00:36:46.674 --> 00:36:49.544
Although I knew it was
all gonna be all right.

906
00:36:49.577 --> 00:36:52.714
Hey. maybe we don't tell
your mom about this.

907
00:36:52.747 --> 00:36:53.848
You know. we just
keep it a bro thing.

908
00:36:53.881 --> 00:36:56.450
So we can--
- Stop. Just stop.

909
00:36:56.483 --> 00:36:57.985
Everything that you do.
everything that you say

910
00:36:58.019 --> 00:37:01.789
is just so selfish. so toxic.

911
00:37:01.823 --> 00:37:04.592
You haven't done one fatherly
thing for me in my entire life.

912
00:37:04.625 --> 00:37:05.827
All you care about is yourself.

913
00:37:05.860 --> 00:37:08.863
And I'm just sick of it.

914
00:37:08.896 --> 00:37:10.998
I'm done with you forever.

915
00:37:11.032 --> 00:37:12.600
- What?

916
00:37:20.373 --> 00:37:22.944
- So we met with
all 27 defendants.

917
00:37:22.977 --> 00:37:24.212
- It's the craziest thing.

918
00:37:24.244 --> 00:37:26.814
We tried our hardest. none of
them would accept a plea deal.

919
00:37:26.848 --> 00:37:27.849
- Not a one.

920
00:37:27.882 --> 00:37:29.349
- Well. I hope you've
kept your weekends clear.

921
00:37:29.382 --> 00:37:31.318
because now you've
got 27 trials

922
00:37:31.351 --> 00:37:32.352
you're gonna
need to prepare for.

923
00:37:34.387 --> 00:37:36.490
- About that.

924
00:37:36.524 --> 00:37:37.491
I quit.

925
00:37:37.525 --> 00:37:39.594
And I'd say best of luck.

926
00:37:39.627 --> 00:37:41.763
but I hope
you fail spectacularly.

927
00:37:41.796 --> 00:37:43.030
Sorry. Sean. I just can't.

928
00:37:43.064 --> 00:37:43.965
- No. no worries.

929
00:37:43.998 --> 00:37:46.466
I can't either.

930
00:37:46.500 --> 00:37:48.603
I quit too.

931
00:37:48.636 --> 00:37:49.871
Hey. what do you
think of the law firm

932
00:37:49.904 --> 00:37:50.872
of Del Monte and Evers?

933
00:37:50.905 --> 00:37:52.372
- Well. you haven't
worked a day in your life

934
00:37:52.405 --> 00:37:53.508
as a defense attorney.

935
00:37:53.541 --> 00:37:56.476
Evers and Del Monte.

936
00:37:56.511 --> 00:37:57.477
- Turn to the right.

937
00:37:57.512 --> 00:37:58.478
- Way ahead of you.

938
00:37:58.513 --> 00:38:00.347
Not my first rodeo.

939
00:38:00.380 --> 00:38:02.382
- Now we just need your
clothes for evidence.

940
00:38:02.415 --> 00:38:05.720
and then you're free to go.

941
00:38:05.753 --> 00:38:07.655
- After everything
that happened?

942
00:38:07.688 --> 00:38:09.489
- The DA may still
press charges.

943
00:38:09.524 --> 00:38:12.627
but it was pretty clear
you were under duress.

944
00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:14.762
- I really wanted this time
to be different.

945
00:38:14.796 --> 00:38:17.865
I was gonna buy a Dash a car
with a Tiger Bear on it

946
00:38:17.899 --> 00:38:20.034
to make up for lost time.
you know.

947
00:38:20.067 --> 00:38:21.869
But he's right.

948
00:38:21.903 --> 00:38:23.638
I screw everything up.

949
00:38:23.671 --> 00:38:25.039
He's better off without me.

950
00:38:25.072 --> 00:38:27.809
- Probably.

951
00:38:27.842 --> 00:38:31.546
I've had some experience
with bad fathers and the love

952
00:38:31.579 --> 00:38:33.681
that sons feel for them
no matter how many times

953
00:38:33.714 --> 00:38:35.683
they get their hearts broken.

954
00:38:35.716 --> 00:38:37.417
And unless you're
willing to change.

955
00:38:37.450 --> 00:38:41.421
and I mean really change.

956
00:38:41.454 --> 00:38:43.423
the best thing
you can do for Dash

957
00:38:43.456 --> 00:38:46.393
is just leave him
the hell alone.

958
00:38:54.969 --> 00:38:57.672
- What were you thinking?

959
00:38:57.705 --> 00:38:59.707
- I'm fine. Thanks for asking.

960
00:38:59.740 --> 00:39:00.842
- Do you know how close
you were to becoming

961
00:39:00.875 --> 00:39:02.442
a missing person yourself?

962
00:39:02.475 --> 00:39:03.845
If she would have
succeeded in killing you.

963
00:39:03.878 --> 00:39:05.079
how would I have known?

964
00:39:05.112 --> 00:39:06.948
The first thing she'd do
is destroy your phone.

965
00:39:06.981 --> 00:39:09.116
So when I pulled your
last known location.

966
00:39:09.150 --> 00:39:11.118
it would be your building.

967
00:39:11.152 --> 00:39:12.720
So to me and the world.
you were home.

968
00:39:12.753 --> 00:39:14.822
and then you vanished.

969
00:39:14.856 --> 00:39:16.858
- I see that now.

970
00:39:16.891 --> 00:39:18.860
It's just. I figured I'd stop
by and ask a few questions.

971
00:39:18.893 --> 00:39:20.628
- We have protocols
for a reason.

972
00:39:22.597 --> 00:39:24.599
- Yes. sir.

973
00:39:24.632 --> 00:39:28.002
I let my best intentions
obscure my judgment

974
00:39:28.035 --> 00:39:31.572
proving I still have a lot
to learn about this job.

975
00:39:31.606 --> 00:39:35.743
You know. but if I can be
so bold as to ask a favor...

976
00:39:39.647 --> 00:39:41.749
- You can ask.

977
00:39:41.782 --> 00:39:44.552
- I remain undaunted.

978
00:39:44.585 --> 00:39:46.621
So if a file
comes across your desk

979
00:39:46.654 --> 00:39:49.156
that gives you a feeling.
call me.

980
00:39:49.190 --> 00:39:53.628
I am happy to run down any lead
I can for you free of charge.

981
00:39:57.798 --> 00:39:59.867
- Deal.

982
00:39:59.901 --> 00:40:01.969
And for what it's worth...

983
00:40:02.003 --> 00:40:03.905
I'm glad you're okay.

984
00:40:19.520 --> 00:40:22.056
- Your dad's gone.
and your mom's on her way.

985
00:40:22.089 --> 00:40:23.090
- Cool.

986
00:40:25.893 --> 00:40:28.162
- Do you wanna
talk about anything?

987
00:40:28.195 --> 00:40:30.463
- Uh. not really.

988
00:40:30.497 --> 00:40:33.901
I think I'm a little
talked out for once.

989
00:40:33.935 --> 00:40:34.769
- Understood.

990
00:40:37.705 --> 00:40:41.208
You know. at the risk
of sounding overly earnest.

991
00:40:41.242 --> 00:40:43.945
you're a very special
young man.

992
00:40:43.978 --> 00:40:47.515
despite--or maybe
even because of what

993
00:40:47.548 --> 00:40:49.750
your father's put you through.

994
00:40:49.784 --> 00:40:51.953
Now. I know you know
that you're not him

995
00:40:51.986 --> 00:40:56.157
in any way. shape. or form.

996
00:40:56.190 --> 00:41:00.061
but I also know that
family pain is emotional

997
00:41:00.094 --> 00:41:03.597
and not intellectual.

998
00:41:05.866 --> 00:41:08.202
I'm just trying to say.

999
00:41:08.235 --> 00:41:11.038
if you ever need a reminder
of this conversation.

1000
00:41:11.072 --> 00:41:13.541
you have my number.

1001
00:41:13.574 --> 00:41:15.710
- Thanks.

1002
00:41:15.743 --> 00:41:17.511
And just to be clear.
you're saying

1003
00:41:17.545 --> 00:41:19.213
I can call you every morning
at the crack of dawn

1004
00:41:19.246 --> 00:41:20.681
just to tell me I'm awesome?

1005
00:41:20.715 --> 00:41:22.717
- No.
- Every other morning?

1006
00:41:22.750 --> 00:41:24.986
- Twice a week. final offer.

1007
00:41:25.019 --> 00:41:26.654
- I can live with that--

1008
